**Using a Discord Bot with Radar Functionality:**

1. **Create a Discord Bot:** Visit the Discord Developer Portal and create a new bot.
2. **Install a Radar Library:** Implement a radar library, such as [node-radar](https://github.com/Explonymous/node-radar), into your bot. This library can generate a textual representation of a radar scan.
3. **Command Handling:** Add a command listener to your bot that triggers when a user enters a specific command in a specified channel.
4. **Generate Radar Image:** When the command is received, have your bot generate a radar image using the coordinates and settings passed in by the command.
5. **Send Radar Image:** Send the generated radar image as a message in the same channel where the command was received.

**Controlling the Boat with Server-Side Logic:**

1. **Create a Boat Object:** Implement a server-side object to represent the boat's location and movement.
2. **Event-Based Movement:** Handle incoming command messages from the bot. When a command is received, update the boat object's location based on the command parameters.
3. **Broadcast Boat Location:** Send a message to the bot with the updated boat location.

**Integrating the Boat and Radar Systems:**

1. **Connect Bot and Server:** Establish a connection between your boat movement logic and the Discord bot.
2. **Update Radar on Boat Movement:** When the boat location is updated, trigger the bot to generate and send a new radar image to the corresponding channel.

**Example:**

```
// Discord Bot
client.on("message", async (message) => {
  if (message.content.startsWith("!move")) {
    const args = message.content.split(" ");
    updateBoatLocation(args[1], args[2]); // Call server-side function to update boat location
  }
});

// Server-Side Boat Movement Logic
function updateBoatLocation(x, y) {
  boat.x = x;
  boat.y = y;
  broadcastBoatLocation(); // Send boat location to Discord bot
}

function broadcastBoatLocation() {
  bot.sendMessage(JSON.stringify(boat)); // Send boat location to bot in JSON format
}

// Bot Radar System
client.on("message", async (message) => {
  if (message.content.startsWith("!radar")) {
    const args = message.content.split(" ");
    const image = generateRadarImage(boat.x, boat.y, args[1]); // Generate radar image based on boat location and input
    message.channel.send(image);
  }
});
```
